					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up in the second <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> of the Sōmanāthēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>[Baṅkidēva], 1296 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This damaged record refers to <hi rend="bold">Baṁkidēvarasa</hi> who may probably be the Āḷupa chief and other officials who met in the <hi rend="italic">hiriya-aramane</hi> (big palace) at <hi rend="bold">Maṅgaḷūru.</hi> It seems to register a gift, the purport of which is not however, clear.</p>						

						<p>If may be assigned on palaeographical grounds to about the 13th century is dated the cyclic year <hi rend="bold">Durmukhi, Siṁha 27, Thursday.</hi> The <hi rend="italic">tithi</hi> corresponds <hi rend="bold">to 1296 A.D., August 24.</hi> The weekday, however was Thursday, falling in the reign period of Baṅkidēva. </p>						

						</summary>
